			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hi Xalmat! Following up on this thread <a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?t=11214" target="_blank">http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?t=11214</a> I decided to make a Library entry... Please copy/paste and add this to the library! <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="Very Happy" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
=== Doing Loot Duty on Raids (works in groups too!) ===
<br />
Magicians are the superior Main Looters of EQ. Rogues sometimes are perceived as being able to do it but lets not kid ourself, unless SOE does some major class rebalancing they simply wont cut it. (Observe: This is not a thread discussing class balance and if Rogues should be able to Main Loot on a raids, that is left for other forums.)
<br />

<br />
As a Main Looter you must need to leave as much as you can in bank, and make sure you have as many free slots as possible. Besides a few tinkers bags you need some free inventory slots for norent bags. (Spell: Gift of Xev, not the heavy crap-bag from Grandmaster Tradeskill Award.)
<br />

<br />
The following spells should be memmed:
<br />
* Rathe's Son - Keep mobs from running away with their loot.
<br />
* Gift of Xev - So you can bring in new bags quickly.
<br />
* Summon Ring of Flight - So you quickly can refresh levitate. Need to reach high sometimes.
<br />
* Protection of Calliav - Need to protect pet so it survives and you can /assist it.
<br />
* Planar Renewal - Need to protect pet so it survives and you can /assist it.
<br />
* Velocity - So pet can keep up with you when you are looting.
<br />
* Eye of Zomm - Look around for missed corpses during fight.
<br />

<br />
Optional: Wuggans Line - Usually you also have a Rogue/Wizzie/Priest in "Team Loot" so they can aid you with their abilities under the Master Looters coordination. The same people should also have a lot of inventory slots open so they can carry the bags they give you. (Remember to give em the non-stackable stuff.)
<br />

<br />
=== Basics ===
<br />
The first thing you need to set up is the Loot Hotbuttons... Usually you will need two in order to be a professional Main Looter.
<br />

<br />
1. Loot Noname Corpse (Referred to as LNC button)
<br />
/target a_
<br />
/target an_
<br />
/pause 2
<br />
/loot
<br />

<br />
2. Loot Pet-killed Corpse (Referred to as LPC button)
<br />
/target pet
<br />
/pause 1
<br />
/assist
<br />
/pause 1
<br />
/loot
<br />

<br />
The best effect and exact pause time depends on your lag. It might be necessary for you to adjust this in certain situations and even add two more hotbuttons with bigger pauses according to RaidLag.
<br />

<br />
You sometimes see LC (Loot-Coordinator), in /rsay telling everyone to switch to RLNC or RLPC. It means the network lag is high, and they should switch to using Raidlag-Loot buttons with increased pause-values.
<br />

<br />
Optional Hotbutton
<br />
/autoi
<br />
/autoi
<br />
/autoi
<br />
/autoi
<br />
/autoi
<br />

<br />
If you by mistake left-click instead of right-click items, and load up a lot of items on your cursor... slam this button to quickly dispatch them to inventory.
<br />

<br />
=== Important commands ===
<br />
/lootnodrop always - Always display YES/NO question for nodrop items.
<br />
/hidecorpse none - Make sure you can see all corpses.
<br />
/autosplit off - Turn off autosplit
<br />
/fastdrop off - Make sure you dont drop anything by mistake.
<br />
/petition - If something is wrong with the loot, like droprate or anything else.
<br />
/gems - Gives you something to do during long VT fights while waiting for the corpse.
<br />

<br />
Remember looting is a teamwork... stackabale items stack! You need to exchange bags with stackable stuff with others in the loot teams so you waste as few slots as possible. Study the zone BEFORE you enter, and plan who will carry what stackable items so you can quickly exchange bags between you and make sure you stack items as efficiently as possible.
<br />

<br />
==== Q &amp; A ====
<br />
Q: What buffs should I ask for?
<br />

<br />
A: These are the important ones... 
<br />
1 - Talisman of the Diaku (Need that strength for carrying coins.)
<br />
2 - Ferine Avatar (More STR, make sure the Shaman times it, you shouldn't have to ask.)
<br />
3 - Unfailing Reverence (Need Charisma when selling.)
<br />
4 - Flight of Eagles/Spirit of the Shrew (Move fast between corpses.)
<br />
---
<br />
Q: What equipment should I aim for?
<br />

<br />
A: These are some equipment your guild should prioritize for you.
<br />
1 - Very Large Coin Purse (http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=6099)
<br />
2 - Charisma items (Example: <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=12043)" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=12043)</a>
<br />
3 - Anything with Strength on it.
<br />
---
<br />
Q: What player skills are required to become an efficient Main Looter?
<br />

<br />
A: Slamming above hotbuttons, right clicking, moving around quickly and get a feel for the range of the /loot command. A good place to practice is Black Burrow. One of the most important things though is a STABLE connection... don't want to be away for 30 min and come back and discover your bags poofed. Or come back after 8 minutes and discover all your groupmates crying because low level corpse has poofed and none was there to loot it.
<br />
---
<br />
Q: People sometimes wants me to do Debuff, DS, Nuke, or summon them stuff. How can I be an efficient looter and also do all the other tasks?
<br />

<br />
A: You can't! Just explain to them you are busy looting and Shaman should debuff, Druids should DS, Wizzies should nuke, and if they need any gear they should have bought it in the Bazaar pre-raid. You are all there for the loot, right? If you screw up your task the raid will leave without loot and the whole raid will be lost. You might want to make a hotbutton you can slam when getting tells - "/r Busy LOOTING!!! Pester someone else will ya!"
<br />
---
<br />
Q: Our guild need more looters but we lack mages... what other class can step up to the task and become a good looter?
<br />

<br />
A: Actually none. For a successful raiding guild it's imperative that you have at least 2-3 mages for coordinating looting. You may want to include other classes in the loot team though, for help with carrying coins or bags as they fill up and dedicated buffers for the loot team.
<br />
---
<br />

<br />
"All classes are not considered balanced until they can come close to the Magicians ability to loot." /AbzorEQ</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
